WEBVTT

02:14.886 --> 02:16.304
Tommy?

02:19.224 --> 02:21.768
Tommy, are you awake?

02:24.563 --> 02:26.690
I saw your missing boat outside.

02:29.276 --> 02:30.694
I'm gonna get it for you.

02:33.530 --> 02:35.949
Mrs. Summers?

02:36.032 --> 02:37.993
Are you sure I should go?

02:38.076 --> 02:39.744
I don't mind staying.

02:39.828 --> 02:41.746
No, it's fine. You should go home.

02:42.414 --> 02:44.040
I'll check on the kids later.

02:44.124 --> 02:45.876
Okay, Mrs. Summers.

02:46.001 --> 02:47.335
I'll see you tomorrow.

03:08.315 --> 03:09.649
There you are.

04:03.036 --> 04:04.246
Rebecca?

04:05.497 --> 04:06.581
What are you doing?

04:18.593 --> 04:19.886
Sorry, Mom.

04:19.970 --> 04:21.346
I didn't mean...

04:26.935 --> 04:28.228
Mom?

05:24.117 --> 05:26.244
<i>Temagami. Temagami.</i>

05:26.369 --> 05:28.747
<i>Temagami. Temagami...</i>

05:32.167 --> 05:34.628
Mom! Mom! Mom!

05:34.711 --> 05:36.254
Help!

06:00.737 --> 06:03.406
<i>Brewers played
extra innings with the Marlins yesterday.</i>

06:03.490 --> 06:04.491
<i>They fell in 12.</i>

06:04.574 --> 06:08.078
<i>One-one. Foul ball up the first baseline,
and it is two strikes.</i>

06:08.662 --> 06:12.123
<i>Brewers are eight and nine
in extra-inning games so far this season.</i>

06:12.249 --> 06:13.708
<i>Hoping to keep that streak alive.</i>

06:14.834 --> 06:16.378
Ray,  they're ready for us.

06:24.344 --> 06:25.637
Dad.

06:26.221 --> 06:27.430
You okay?

06:28.515 --> 06:31.226
Yeah. Yeah, I'm good.

06:31.309 --> 06:33.520
Give me a head start.
I'll meet you inside.

06:39.067 --> 06:41.111
This has got every single thing
that you asked for.

06:41.194 --> 06:43.446
It has 24-hour emergency call service.

06:44.072 --> 06:45.824
Right? Which is great.

06:45.907 --> 06:48.577
It's got single-level bedrooms.

06:48.660 --> 06:51.037
It's got bath...
All the bathrooms have handrails.

06:51.121 --> 06:52.914
And you're just minutes away

06:52.998 --> 06:55.834
from one of the best medical facilities
in the Twin Cities.

06:55.917 --> 06:56.918
Yeah.

06:57.043 --> 06:58.837
It's... I mean,
it's really kind of perfect lease

06:58.920 --> 07:00.755
for when you just need
a little extra help.

07:01.548 --> 07:02.883
Do you not like it?

07:02.966 --> 07:04.885
- Well, it's nice.
Are you... Are you looking

07:04.968 --> 07:06.720
for a place to throw the ball around?

07:07.929 --> 07:09.681
Is there any chance
that you're gonna bring

07:09.806 --> 07:12.517
that Waller swing here
once you get better?

07:14.603 --> 07:16.479
I'm sorry. I Google all my clients,

07:16.563 --> 07:18.732
and it's just not every day
that I get a...

07:18.815 --> 07:20.275
A big-league third baseman.

07:20.358 --> 07:21.818
Yeah, no. I, um...

07:22.444 --> 07:24.279
I'm just focused on getting better now

07:24.362 --> 07:25.864
and spending some time at home

07:25.947 --> 07:27.324
- and being with family.
- Well, you know what?

07:27.407 --> 07:29.868
You can spend some of that
baseball money right here.

07:29.951 --> 07:32.662
You can't put a price on peace of mind.

07:32.787 --> 07:35.332
Yeah. Yeah, well,
apparently, here you can.

07:35.457 --> 07:37.042
It's 4,200 bucks.

07:37.167 --> 07:40.420
Oh, just... You know what? In the kitchen.
Come here. I want to show you.

07:40.503 --> 07:41.963
There's this accessible design.

07:42.047 --> 07:44.633
And I don't know who did it,
but I think I want one myself.

07:44.716 --> 07:45.967
- I'll tell you that much.
You guys like it or...

07:46.051 --> 07:47.552
Yeah.
I might be your neighbor.

08:23.964 --> 08:25.423
Wait, wait. Honey, honey.

08:25.507 --> 08:26.758
- Wait, stop, stop.
- What?

08:26.841 --> 08:28.677
Honey, stop, stop, stop. Look.

08:28.760 --> 08:30.303
Look. Look.

08:32.471 --> 08:33.723
Huh.

08:34.014 --> 08:35.725
I would've shown you this place,

08:35.809 --> 08:37.726
but it didn't really meet your checklist.

08:37.811 --> 08:39.854
- And this is not a rental, right?
- I know.

08:39.937 --> 08:41.773
- We were just curious.
- Okay.

08:41.855 --> 08:44.818
Right, well, it's only one owner
for the last couple decades.

08:44.901 --> 08:48.321
And, uh, you know,
it needs just a little work, I think.

08:48.405 --> 08:51.157
But it's not gonna be on the market
very long at this price.

08:51.283 --> 08:54.703
Oh, and you're in a great school district
with Harold Holt.

08:54.786 --> 08:56.121
That's where I start in the fall.

08:56.204 --> 08:58.456
No, really? Oh, I'm a proud alum myself.

08:58.540 --> 08:59.624
Go, Lake Trout.

09:01.585 --> 09:03.503
And what subject do you teach there?

09:03.628 --> 09:05.297
Oh, no. I'm just in the admin office

09:05.422 --> 09:08.258
while I finish my degree online
for special education.

09:09.342 --> 09:11.344
Oh. Good for you. Good for you.

09:11.428 --> 09:13.638
Well, it's never too late
to follow your dream.

09:14.222 --> 09:17.100
Too awesome.

09:17.642 --> 09:18.685
Yeah.

09:18.768 --> 09:21.771
Oh, my gosh. This is amazing.

09:21.897 --> 09:24.107
- What is that? The fruit baskets.

09:24.900 --> 09:26.318
Where did Ray get off to?

09:26.443 --> 09:27.652
I didn't see him.

09:29.863 --> 09:31.239
There you are.

09:31.364 --> 09:32.866
Hey.

09:32.949 --> 09:34.367
There's a pool.

09:37.203 --> 09:38.872
I used to be scared of pools.

09:40.665 --> 09:43.501
My dad pushed me
into one of the training tanks

09:43.585 --> 09:45.545
at Fort Benning when I was three.

09:45.629 --> 09:46.755
Mm-hmm.

09:46.838 --> 09:48.506
Sink or swim.

09:48.590 --> 09:50.091
I guess I swam.

09:52.177 --> 09:53.511
I always wanted a pool.

09:54.679 --> 09:56.806
When we were kids,
we used to go down the street,

09:56.890 --> 09:59.184
break into the KOA, go swimming.

09:59.351 --> 10:02.270
We used to pretend that
we were the rich kids from the suburbs.

10:03.897 --> 10:05.690
Hey, Mom, can we get lunch?

10:05.774 --> 10:07.859
Yeah, I'm ready to go.
Can we get some food?

10:07.943 --> 10:09.110
Come on, old man.

10:10.028 --> 10:11.571
Before we get too nostalgic.

10:45.021 --> 10:47.566
<i>Familiar face
makes his way down to the plate.</i>

10:47.649 --> 10:49.526
<i>What a story this has been, folks.</i>

10:50.026 --> 10:51.778
<i>After a year battling illness,</i>

10:51.861 --> 10:53.780
<i>Ray Waller is trying to do the impossible</i>

10:53.863 --> 10:55.824
<i>with a Major League comeback.</i>

10:57.534 --> 10:58.577
<i>Glider inside.</i>

10:58.660 --> 10:59.869
<i>Waller digs for it...</i>

11:01.329 --> 11:03.081
<i>- and connects!</i>

11:03.164 --> 11:05.208
<i>It's a deep ball into far center field,</i>

11:05.292 --> 11:06.960
<i>and it is gone!</i>

11:21.766 --> 11:22.934
Dad!

11:23.059 --> 11:24.978
Mom, hurry! Dad fell in!

11:26.563 --> 11:28.815
Ray, what happened? Are you okay?

11:28.899 --> 11:30.567
- Dad? What happened?
Yeah.

11:30.650 --> 11:31.735
Mom, is he okay?

11:31.818 --> 11:33.737
- Just breathe. It's okay.
-  I'm fine.

11:33.820 --> 11:35.280
- Mom, his cane.
- Yep.

11:35.363 --> 11:37.616
- Izzy, give me... Help me here.
- Yep.

11:37.699 --> 11:38.992
- Yeah.
You got it?

11:39.492 --> 11:40.660
Okay.

11:42.704 --> 11:43.747
- You got it?
Okay.

11:43.872 --> 11:45.832
Yeah?
Yeah. Okay.

11:55.217 --> 11:58.011
How long has it been
since your last episode?

11:58.094 --> 11:59.971
Well, it wasn't really an episode,

12:00.055 --> 12:01.348
- I don't think. It's like...

12:01.473 --> 12:03.308
At spring training about six months ago.

12:03.808 --> 12:08.355
My recommendation
is to escalate the diagnosis

12:08.438 --> 12:11.024
to secondary progressive MS.

12:11.107 --> 12:13.693
No, but the doctor said he was stabilizing

12:13.777 --> 12:16.196
and that it's about managing now.

12:16.279 --> 12:19.115
It's better to have
a more accurate diagnosis.

12:19.616 --> 12:20.992
- Are you in PT?
- No...

12:21.076 --> 12:23.370
Um, well, I mean,
I'm throwing the ball around

12:23.453 --> 12:25.163
in the front yard with the kids,
and, like, that.

12:25.247 --> 12:27.958
We just got insurance
through the school where I'm working.

12:28.041 --> 12:29.501
Yeah.
- Forget baseball.

12:29.584 --> 12:32.837
For now, we need to find
a low-impact activity

12:32.921 --> 12:34.297
that you can do every day.

12:34.381 --> 12:36.466
Walking, yoga.

12:36.550 --> 12:39.386
Most therapists recommend swimming.

12:39.469 --> 12:41.721
Look, I know it feels like
your whole world

12:41.805 --> 12:43.265
is turning upside down.

12:44.391 --> 12:46.851
It's going to take sacrifice
from you both,

12:46.935 --> 12:49.229
but you can build a good life together.

12:49.312 --> 12:51.815
First, you have to let go of the old one.

12:53.358 --> 12:56.486
Use the wheelchair for the next few days
while you regulate,

12:56.570 --> 12:58.738
and I will bring you back in next week.

13:03.577 --> 13:06.830
Honey, if we rent that townhome,
it'd be like living in a hospital.

13:10.417 --> 13:12.085
I don't want to be the sick guy anymore.

13:12.168 --> 13:13.378
But you're sick, Ray.

13:13.503 --> 13:15.255
- We need to deal with that head-on.
- I know. I just don't want it

13:15.338 --> 13:17.257
to define our whole life now.

13:19.593 --> 13:21.219
What about that other house?

13:22.053 --> 13:25.056
The kids will love it, with all that room.

13:25.140 --> 13:26.182
And with a swimming pool,

13:26.266 --> 13:29.185
we'll have water therapy
in our own backyard.

13:40.697 --> 13:42.908
You know I want our own place.

13:43.825 --> 13:46.828
I'm tired of the kids changing schools,

13:46.912 --> 13:49.706
making new friends
every time you get traded.

13:50.624 --> 13:53.877
I want us to put down roots, you know?

13:55.170 --> 13:58.006
I just need to know
that you want that, too.

13:58.089 --> 13:59.090
I do.

14:00.425 --> 14:01.468
Eve.

14:04.721 --> 14:06.223
I want that, too.

14:07.432 --> 14:08.642
I promise.

14:11.686 --> 14:14.189
Also, you know what else
I was wondering about?

14:14.314 --> 14:17.943
Do you have that black bikini still?

14:18.026 --> 14:19.277
You know which one I'm talking about?

14:19.361 --> 14:20.820
- With the crisscross straps?
- Guy's in a hospital.

14:20.904 --> 14:22.364
This is what he's thinking.

14:22.864 --> 14:25.575
<i>This summer I went swimming</i>

14:25.659 --> 14:27.994
<i>This summer I might have drowned</i>

14:28.078 --> 14:30.747
<i>But I held my breath and I kicked my feet</i>

14:30.830 --> 14:33.458
<i>And I moved my arms around</i>

14:33.541 --> 14:34.751
<i>I moved my arms around...</i>

14:34.834 --> 14:37.045
Hey, there you are, Cider.

14:37.128 --> 14:38.421
Come here, buddy.

14:38.922 --> 14:40.382
How do you like our new home?

14:40.465 --> 14:42.842
Isn't it awesome? It's so big, right?

14:42.926 --> 14:45.303
<i>Chlorine my eyes,
I'm a self-destructive fool...</i>

14:45.387 --> 14:46.930
Izzy, I'll see you later.
Okay.

14:47.013 --> 14:48.682
Good luck.
- Thanks.

14:48.765 --> 14:49.808
You got it.
- Yeah.

14:49.891 --> 14:51.685
Oh, wait, wait, wait.
- What?

14:51.768 --> 14:53.019
Oh, thanks.

14:53.144 --> 14:55.021
- See you later, dipshit.
See you, barf bag.

14:55.981 --> 14:57.357
Think you're gonna go out this year?

14:57.440 --> 15:00.443
Yeah. Dad says
I'm about to hit my growth spurt.

15:01.820 --> 15:03.446
Actually, wait.

15:04.197 --> 15:06.449
Yeah. I think you're hitting it right now.

15:08.868 --> 15:11.079
Here. Wait, wait. I got it.

15:12.247 --> 15:14.624
<i>The old Australian crawl</i>

15:14.708 --> 15:17.252
<i>This summer I went swimming</i>

15:17.377 --> 15:18.670
<i>This summer I might have drowned...</i>

15:18.753 --> 15:20.505
Hey, how tall are you?

15:21.506 --> 15:22.507
Look, um...

15:22.591 --> 15:24.175
Can you just put your arm up real quick?

15:24.259 --> 15:26.553
Like, yeah. Just like that.

15:26.636 --> 15:27.971
Yeah, you have a great wingspan.

15:29.222 --> 15:30.223
Thanks.

15:30.307 --> 15:31.516
You should come on Friday.

15:32.642 --> 15:34.644
- Okay.
- My name's Ronin.

15:35.186 --> 15:37.939
Hey, you should come on Friday,
for real. It's gonna be dope.

15:39.649 --> 15:42.819
<i>Hey-ee!</i>

15:56.166 --> 15:57.918
Does it smell weird to you guys?

15:58.043 --> 15:59.961
Nah, you're just
turning back into a dog.

16:00.045 --> 16:02.172
Have to take you back to the shelter
where Mom and Dad found you.

16:04.090 --> 16:06.551
What is with the PYX 106 playlist?

16:06.635 --> 16:08.178
I'm bringing back the classics, babe.

16:08.261 --> 16:10.388
I like it, Dad.
Hey, El, I...

16:11.056 --> 16:12.849
I talked with your coach at orientation.

16:12.933 --> 16:16.394
He thought it might be good
if I come and help with practice.

16:16.478 --> 16:18.230
I thought it might be kinda fun, right?

16:18.313 --> 16:19.898
Yeah, Dad. This is my year, right?

16:20.440 --> 16:21.691
Yeah.

16:21.775 --> 16:22.901
It is.

16:23.401 --> 16:25.153
I think I'm going out for the swim team.

16:25.779 --> 16:26.821
Ooh!
Really?

16:26.947 --> 16:28.782
Yeah.
That's great, Iz.

16:28.907 --> 16:30.492
- Yeah, you're gonna be a natural.

16:30.575 --> 16:33.620
That trophy bat, that came alive
the day you were born.

16:33.703 --> 16:34.788
Mm-hmm.

16:34.871 --> 16:38.333
I absolutely launched one into the Bay.

16:38.750 --> 16:39.793
Pop!

16:39.876 --> 16:41.002
Splash.

16:41.086 --> 16:43.797
It was the ninth inning,
and I was at the plate,

16:45.048 --> 16:46.049
and I don't know what it was.

16:46.883 --> 16:49.135
Just this sense of strength came over me.

16:50.053 --> 16:51.471
I knew it.

16:51.555 --> 16:52.931
I knew it right then.

16:53.056 --> 16:54.683
- My Izzy is...

16:55.100 --> 16:56.142
Dad?

16:56.226 --> 16:57.811
- Oh, my gosh.
What happened?

16:57.936 --> 16:59.104
- Ray?
Are you okay?

16:59.229 --> 17:00.689
God, I sliced it pretty good.
- What happened?

17:00.772 --> 17:01.982
- Ah...
- Oh, that looks...

17:02.065 --> 17:03.233
Oh, God.

17:03.942 --> 17:05.610
- Oh, my gosh.
Ew.

17:05.694 --> 17:07.028
- What is that?
Oh, God.

17:07.111 --> 17:08.196
Be careful.

17:09.948 --> 17:11.283
Is that supposed to happen?

17:11.366 --> 17:12.449
I don't think so.

17:13.201 --> 17:14.202
<i>Is it safe?</i>

17:14.285 --> 17:16.454
No pool is absolutely safe.

17:16.538 --> 17:18.039
But you see that cap?

17:18.122 --> 17:19.457
That's a wellhead.

17:20.041 --> 17:24.545
I-I've never seen an actual
spring-fed pool before in person,

17:24.629 --> 17:26.172
but you're tapped into groundwater.

17:26.256 --> 17:27.883
- I'm talking aquiclude.

17:28.008 --> 17:30.385
That's some sublevel aquifer shit.

17:30.468 --> 17:31.887
What does that mean?
- Yeah, what does that mean?

17:31.970 --> 17:33.263
I'm about to tell you what that means.

17:33.388 --> 17:35.599
That means natural filtration,

17:35.682 --> 17:38.602
geothermal heating, the whole shebang.

17:38.727 --> 17:41.479
Yeah, we'll give it a shock,
but these spring pools

17:41.563 --> 17:43.523
are supposed to work miracles
on your skin.

17:43.648 --> 17:45.901
This whole area
had natural pools all around.

17:45.984 --> 17:47.903
Wellness centers, health spas.

17:48.028 --> 17:49.529
That's great. Lucky us, huh?

17:49.654 --> 17:50.780
Yeah.

17:50.864 --> 17:52.741
- It's funny, isn't it, though?
- Uh-huh.

17:52.824 --> 17:54.034
I mean...

17:54.784 --> 17:57.037
We evolved out of the water

17:57.162 --> 17:59.748
and some part of our reptilian brain knows

17:59.873 --> 18:03.168
we're not supposed to be there
anymore, but...

18:03.668 --> 18:06.671
I guess that's why
we try to tame it so hard.

18:08.465 --> 18:10.967
It's like trying to conquer death...

18:11.051 --> 18:12.052
- Whoa, whoa.
Jesus. Be careful.

18:12.135 --> 18:14.554
Are you okay?
- God, sorry.

18:14.679 --> 18:15.764
Butterfingers.

18:16.598 --> 18:17.599
What an idiot.

18:17.682 --> 18:19.434
All right, well, here's your invoice.

18:20.101 --> 18:21.186
I'll come back tomorrow.

18:21.269 --> 18:23.021
You should be set up by next week.

18:23.146 --> 18:24.898
- Okay.
- Great. Thanks.

18:24.981 --> 18:26.566
Hey, Gecko, let's wrap it up.

18:26.650 --> 18:28.193
Come on. Let's boogie, baby.

18:31.863 --> 18:33.823
All right, we're good to go!

18:46.962 --> 18:48.129
Ready?

18:48.213 --> 18:49.214
Yeah.

18:49.297 --> 18:52.425
<i>One life, I'm gonna live it up...</i>

19:03.603 --> 19:05.397
Come on, Dad. Throw some more.

19:05.480 --> 19:08.233
Hold on. I just got to finish
these exercises.

19:09.568 --> 19:10.944
Are you watching this?

19:11.027 --> 19:13.947
The water takes all
the strain off my muscles. It's amazing.

19:14.030 --> 19:15.907
Give me those muscles.

19:19.661 --> 19:20.996
They're all down there.

19:21.121 --> 19:22.455
I'll get 'em all in one breath.

19:23.248 --> 19:25.375
Yeah, sure. Why not? Go.

19:27.335 --> 19:28.587
Are you ready?

19:28.670 --> 19:30.213
You know, this is, um...

19:30.338 --> 19:32.549
It's gonna sound crazy,
but I think that maybe getting sick

19:32.632 --> 19:34.134
happened for a reason, you know?

19:35.385 --> 19:37.262
I don't think
I could've walked away healthy.

19:37.387 --> 19:38.430
Look, right here.

19:39.055 --> 19:41.016
You'll always be a baseball player.

19:41.141 --> 19:42.475
I got it fair and square.

19:42.601 --> 19:43.852
But it's not all you are.

19:45.186 --> 19:47.063
It's not why I fell in love with you.

19:47.188 --> 19:48.773
- No?
- No.

19:49.900 --> 19:51.151
Don't look back.

19:52.277 --> 19:53.486
Remember?

19:53.570 --> 19:54.905
This is all we need.

19:56.239 --> 19:58.158
- Right?
- Yeah.

19:59.576 --> 20:00.827
Yeah.

20:05.498 --> 20:06.750
You know my kiss is magic?

20:06.833 --> 20:07.834
Oh, really?

20:07.918 --> 20:09.544
Yep. If we kiss, you'll be healed.

20:09.628 --> 20:10.712
Wow.

20:12.631 --> 20:13.965
Ew, guys.

20:14.090 --> 20:16.134
You know we're here, right?

20:16.218 --> 20:17.219
Okay.

20:17.302 --> 20:18.303
"Oh, I love you so much."
All right.

20:18.386 --> 20:19.387
- Ruined it.
- Done.

20:19.471 --> 20:20.639
- You ruined the moment.

20:20.722 --> 20:21.723
Now you're gonna pay.

20:21.806 --> 20:24.017
So cringe.
- No, Dad. Don't do it, don't do it.

20:24.100 --> 20:25.393
- Please, no.
Could you at least wait

20:25.477 --> 20:27.562
- until we're gone?
No.

20:28.688 --> 20:30.273
<i>It's comin' now...</i>

20:30.357 --> 20:31.358
Dad?

20:31.441 --> 20:33.360
- Dad, no! Please, no!

21:10.355 --> 21:11.481
<i>You can't catch us.</i>

21:11.565 --> 21:13.900
<i>You can't catch us! You can't catch us!</i>

21:13.984 --> 21:15.151
<i>Elliot's mine!</i>

21:16.611 --> 21:18.530
Don't let him go.
- Come on! You can't catch us!

21:18.613 --> 21:22.826
<i>Teachers need to implement
backdoor strategies</i>

21:22.909 --> 21:26.246
<i>because students with ADHD
and deeply feeling kids</i>

21:26.329 --> 21:29.499
<i>can be easily overwhelmed
by sensory stimulation,</i>

21:29.583 --> 21:33.211
<i>and they may shut down
when emotionally dysregulated.</i>

21:34.754 --> 21:36.840
<i>Kids who are struggling with anxiety</i>

21:36.923 --> 21:38.842
<i>- and in-class performance...</i>

21:38.925 --> 21:41.177
<i>- ...they're inclined to...</i>

22:03.992 --> 22:05.619
Hey, what's the matter?

22:07.954 --> 22:09.289
Huh?

22:10.040 --> 22:13.001
You don't want to swim? Hmm?

22:16.338 --> 22:17.756
Pussy.

22:57.796 --> 22:59.631
Ray, you scared me.

24:04.946 --> 24:07.073
<i>His 27th home run this season,</i>

24:07.157 --> 24:09.159
<i>and the crowd is fully back in the game.</i>

24:09.242 --> 24:12.871
<i>So many times, we talk about how momentum
can change with one swing of the bat.</i>

24:12.996 --> 24:14.414
<i>One pitch, one play...</i>

24:21.630 --> 24:22.923
You're all wet.

24:24.674 --> 24:26.509
Were you outside a minute ago?

24:27.636 --> 24:28.970
No.

24:29.054 --> 24:31.890
I think I just fell asleep.

24:34.976 --> 24:38.313
I think we should put in a pool cover
just to be safe.

24:39.564 --> 24:41.816
And we need to check out the lights.

24:41.900 --> 24:44.069
Yeah... Yeah, for sure.

24:45.153 --> 24:46.696
Everything okay?

24:47.113 --> 24:49.866
Yeah. Yeah. Go back to sleep.

25:22.649 --> 25:24.025
<i>Mom! Dad!</i>

25:24.109 --> 25:25.569
Come look!

25:26.653 --> 25:28.822
He probably fell in and got scared.

25:30.991 --> 25:33.326
Well, he... He'll come back
when he's hungry, huh?

25:34.202 --> 25:35.495
We have to find him.

25:36.037 --> 25:38.248
Yeah, that's... We'll go look for him.

25:38.331 --> 25:39.833
We'll find him.

25:39.916 --> 25:41.668
It's okay, Ellie. He'll come back.

25:41.751 --> 25:43.962
Pshh-pshh-pshh-pshh-pshh-pshh-pshh!

25:44.629 --> 25:46.548
- Cider.
Come here, Cider.

25:46.631 --> 25:47.883
Come on, puss.

25:48.800 --> 25:50.468
Cider, where'd you go?

25:51.094 --> 25:52.220
Cider?

25:52.888 --> 25:55.223
Izzy, did you look down there?

25:55.307 --> 25:57.058
No, I didn't check there.

25:57.183 --> 25:58.184
Here, puss.

25:58.268 --> 25:59.686
Maybe he's up in this tree?

26:01.187 --> 26:02.564
Come here, Cider.

26:02.647 --> 26:03.773
Cider.

26:04.816 --> 26:05.859
Cider!

26:07.527 --> 26:09.321
You guys looked inside the house?

26:10.238 --> 26:11.573
Yeah.
Come here, buddy!

26:11.656 --> 26:13.783
Not upstairs, though.
Did you look upstairs?

26:13.909 --> 26:16.328
Again? I promise you,
I already checked upstairs.

26:19.998 --> 26:21.499
Cider!

26:23.001 --> 26:24.419
Here, Cider.

26:25.670 --> 26:27.297
Come on, Cider.

26:28.590 --> 26:30.383
Cider!

26:34.346 --> 26:35.805
Cider.

26:40.227 --> 26:41.436
Cider.

26:43.438 --> 26:44.481
Want some food?

26:48.401 --> 26:49.736
Come on, Cider.

26:55.951 --> 26:57.535
Come on, put your back into it.

26:57.619 --> 26:59.037
We gotta roll it up, make it tight,

26:59.120 --> 27:01.164
so when we roll it back out,
it's all clean and nice.

27:01.248 --> 27:02.791
Keep cranking. One turn at a time.

27:02.874 --> 27:04.709
I'm trying.
- Come on.

27:04.793 --> 27:06.545
Keep going. You strike out,
you keep going.

27:06.628 --> 27:07.963
Isn't that right? Yeah.

27:08.046 --> 27:09.589
- Don't give up. That's the key.

27:09.673 --> 27:11.925
That's the only thing that matters.
Let's go, come on.

27:12.008 --> 27:13.927
Good job. Little wins.

27:14.010 --> 27:15.303
Here we go. Come on.

27:15.387 --> 27:17.389
Be nice to your brother right now.

27:18.598 --> 27:20.475
None of this has been easy on him.

27:20.600 --> 27:23.728
Keep going, keep going. Good job.

27:24.271 --> 27:25.480
There you go. See?

27:25.605 --> 27:27.607
I know it hasn't been easy on you, either.

27:29.734 --> 27:31.528
Oh, no. Baby, I'm fine.

27:31.611 --> 27:33.238
I don't want you worrying about me.

28:04.394 --> 28:05.729
What is that?

29:07.916 --> 29:10.794
Um, s... What... What is it?

29:15.298 --> 29:18.760
I've never seen
such a dramatic improvement

29:18.843 --> 29:20.720
in such a short time.

29:20.845 --> 29:23.056
We need to do more tests,

29:23.890 --> 29:27.185
but it appears there are no new lesions

29:28.353 --> 29:30.188
and the white tissue
is actually improving.

29:30.730 --> 29:33.567
We started the new diet like you said,

29:33.650 --> 29:35.735
and the water therapy and...

29:35.819 --> 29:37.153
Twice a day.

29:38.780 --> 29:39.864
We have a pool.

29:55.714 --> 29:58.383
Hey, Mom,
I finished all my work in study hall.

29:58.466 --> 29:59.467
Can I go swimming?

29:59.551 --> 30:01.553
Okay, but don't go alone.
Ask your dad.

30:08.351 --> 30:10.687
<i>Here's progress report. I, uh...</i>

30:11.313 --> 30:14.274
<i>You all know I was diagnosed with MS
not too long ago,</i>

30:14.357 --> 30:15.817
<i>a little while back.</i>

30:15.901 --> 30:18.612
- Dad?
<i>- I've been able to work out in rehab</i>

30:18.695 --> 30:21.364
<i>and been getting back at it
for the last little while</i>

30:21.448 --> 30:24.284
<i>and I've made a lot of strides
that I'm proud of.</i>

30:24.367 --> 30:26.244
<i>I think that I can show you,</i>

30:26.328 --> 30:28.830
<i>demonstrate my ability
is still at a level that</i>

30:28.914 --> 30:31.708
<i>I'd be able to make an impact
on a team rather quickly.</i>

30:31.791 --> 30:32.918
Hey, pal.

30:35.045 --> 30:36.463
Can you help me out with something?

30:37.631 --> 30:38.632
Yeah.

30:39.174 --> 30:40.675
Can you throw on a 25?

30:50.435 --> 30:52.187
What are you doing with the camera?

30:52.270 --> 30:54.522
Helps me with my training.

31:09.955 --> 31:11.873
Can you dive for coins with me?

31:11.957 --> 31:13.583
Mom says I can't swim alone.

31:18.547 --> 31:19.756
Yeah, um...

31:21.424 --> 31:22.759
Uh...

31:24.302 --> 31:26.513
Yeah. Hey, hand me one of those coins.

31:30.600 --> 31:31.643
Here.

31:34.396 --> 31:36.064
You gotta promise me

31:36.147 --> 31:37.983
you're gonna stay
in the shallow end. Okay?

31:38.066 --> 31:39.192
Okay.

31:39.317 --> 31:40.652
Throw this one in the pool for me.

31:42.404 --> 31:44.698
And I'll come find it. Okay?

31:45.365 --> 31:46.449
All right.

32:30.785 --> 32:32.037
Hey, Dad.

33:30.136 --> 33:31.221
Hello?

33:41.439 --> 33:42.857
I got 'em all in one breath.

33:52.742 --> 33:55.579
Izzy? It's not funny.

33:59.583 --> 34:00.584
Izzy?

34:03.837 --> 34:05.171
I know that's you.

34:09.259 --> 34:10.468
I'm keeping the money.

34:15.265 --> 34:17.475
Okay, I'm going under.

35:05.941 --> 35:07.234
Hello?

35:12.572 --> 35:13.907
Can you hear me?

35:18.286 --> 35:19.704
I need help.

35:24.709 --> 35:26.503
I'm looking for my mom.

35:28.463 --> 35:29.881
Who are you?

35:30.840 --> 35:33.051
My name is Rebecca Summers.

35:36.888 --> 35:38.723
I found your  toy.

36:06.835 --> 36:08.753
Let go of me!

36:14.217 --> 36:15.552
Help!

36:24.060 --> 36:25.103
Mom.

36:27.522 --> 36:28.940
Is someone out here?

36:35.238 --> 36:36.615
Ellie, are you sure?

36:36.698 --> 36:37.991
Her name is Rebecca.

36:38.950 --> 36:41.036
She said she was looking for her mom.

37:06.478 --> 37:10.232
It was probably just a kid
who snuck over the gate. That's all.

37:10.690 --> 37:12.525
Anyway, we have a lock on it now, so...

37:12.609 --> 37:14.444
I didn't see anyone out there.

37:15.528 --> 37:17.239
Maybe he's pretending.

37:18.073 --> 37:19.950
'Cause he doesn't have
any real friends yet.

37:20.033 --> 37:22.994
Remember he talked to that pet gecko
or lizard, or whatever?

37:23.078 --> 37:24.079
He was five.

37:24.162 --> 37:26.248
Yeah, but he talked to him
for months after he died.

37:26.331 --> 37:28.458
He's gonna make friends. He just...

37:28.541 --> 37:30.293
It just takes him time.

37:30.794 --> 37:34.256
Yeah. I'm going to
his practice later today.

37:35.257 --> 37:38.176
So, maybe that'll help, like,
break the ice with the kids.

37:38.718 --> 37:39.803
Yeah.

37:40.428 --> 37:42.681
You should come,
'cause he always plays better

37:42.764 --> 37:44.266
when you're there. He's more himself.

37:46.351 --> 37:47.519
Hmm.

37:48.937 --> 37:51.064
Maybe we should have the team over.

37:51.147 --> 37:53.608
- You know, for a cookout or something?
- Yes.

37:53.692 --> 37:54.776
That's a great idea.

37:54.859 --> 37:56.361
- Yeah?
- Yeah, like a pool party.

37:56.444 --> 37:58.863
That's why I married you,
because you're a genius.

37:58.947 --> 38:00.532
Invite your coworkers, friends, whoever.

38:00.657 --> 38:02.409
- Just "Meet the Wallers," right?
- Mm-hmm.

38:02.492 --> 38:03.743
Sounds great.
Can I invite some friends?

38:03.827 --> 38:05.996
Yes, invite whoever you want.
It's a great idea.

38:06.079 --> 38:07.289
We should invite everybody you know.

38:07.372 --> 38:08.498
- We're a welcoming family.
Stop.

38:08.582 --> 38:10.208
How many people you think
we can fit in the pool?

38:10.292 --> 38:11.459
We're the pool family now.

38:13.169 --> 38:14.379
All right. Get in front of it.

38:15.088 --> 38:16.631
Good. Move it around.

38:16.715 --> 38:18.216
There you go, in front of it,
in front of it.

38:19.092 --> 38:20.677
It's all right. It's all right.

38:20.760 --> 38:22.095
Get in front of it. In front of it.

38:23.638 --> 38:25.515
Come on, wake up, man.

38:25.640 --> 38:27.309
Let's hustle. Let's hustle, boys.

38:27.392 --> 38:29.352
You know what baseball is, right?

38:30.604 --> 38:33.106
It's a stick and a ball

38:33.189 --> 38:35.609
and a bunch of guys wearing long socks.

38:38.111 --> 38:39.321
It's play.

38:40.363 --> 38:42.782
How come it's so easy for Dad and Izzy?

38:42.866 --> 38:44.200
It's not.

38:45.577 --> 38:47.579
Everyone's scared of something.

38:48.121 --> 38:50.749
Izzy used to hate drop-off
in kindergarten.

38:51.541 --> 38:53.877
Every day, I'd wait outside
until I saw her

38:54.002 --> 38:56.338
in the classroom window,
and she'd give me the signal.

38:57.047 --> 38:58.465
- Show him, Iz.
There we go!

38:58.632 --> 39:00.217
Good job, good job.

39:01.760 --> 39:03.136
Green light to swing.

39:03.220 --> 39:04.346
Wait for the ball, boys!

39:04.429 --> 39:05.722
Come on, come on!

39:05.805 --> 39:07.807
- Hey, there he is.
Hey, Coach. Sorry I'm late.

39:08.391 --> 39:10.143
- Hey, guys.
Hey.

39:10.227 --> 39:11.228
All right.

39:11.895 --> 39:13.355
You got this.

39:14.105 --> 39:16.191
Hey, boys, this is Elliot's dad.

39:16.274 --> 39:18.318
He's a former Brewers third baseman,

39:18.401 --> 39:20.320
and he's here to turn you
into all-star hitters.

39:21.321 --> 39:23.490
You got this. You got this. Nice and easy.

39:26.034 --> 39:28.328
You gotta follow through the ball.
Don't just, like, check swing.

39:29.204 --> 39:30.914
- There you go.
- Yes! Nice!

39:30.997 --> 39:32.707
All right. Line drive up the middle.
There you go.

39:32.791 --> 39:34.084
All right, move it around, move it around.

39:34.167 --> 39:36.044
You're bent way over
at the waist, right?

39:36.169 --> 39:37.420
And you turn out with your body.

39:37.504 --> 39:39.464
Don't hit it with your hands.
You turn out with your body.

39:39.548 --> 39:40.840
- All right. Good job.
There you go!

39:40.924 --> 39:42.259
Way to get on top of it. Good job.

39:42.342 --> 39:44.386
Oh, hey, Ray, that's my son, Ty.

39:44.511 --> 39:46.263
Yeah, keep an eye.
He's got good mechanics.

39:46.346 --> 39:47.931
All right, Ty.
Let's see what you got.

39:49.558 --> 39:50.850
- There you go.

39:50.934 --> 39:52.435
Yes, Ty! Yes!

39:52.769 --> 39:54.604
- Good swing. Good hit.
Yeah, I got you, Dad.

39:54.729 --> 39:56.231
- Good job.
Thanks, Mr. Waller.

39:56.314 --> 39:57.482
All right, El, you ready?

39:58.441 --> 39:59.526
Go, Ellie!

39:59.609 --> 40:01.194
All right, let's go.
Hey. Good luck out there, man.

40:01.278 --> 40:02.404
You got this.

40:02.487 --> 40:04.781
Way to go. Good job, Ty.

40:04.864 --> 40:06.283
Hey, Ellie.

40:12.122 --> 40:13.707
All right, Elliot.

40:14.332 --> 40:15.750
All right, come on. You got this.

40:16.585 --> 40:17.836
You got it, Elliot.

40:18.670 --> 40:20.130
- There you go. Nice!
Nice going.

40:20.213 --> 40:22.507
- There you go. All right. Good job.

40:22.591 --> 40:24.175
- Yes, Elliot.
All right.

40:24.301 --> 40:25.552
That's what stepping into the ball does.

40:25.677 --> 40:26.720
You go after it and you get it.

40:26.803 --> 40:27.971
Good job. Way to go.

40:28.054 --> 40:29.639
Try for the other side of the field.
Way to go.

40:29.723 --> 40:30.807
We'll work on it. Don't worry about it.

40:30.891 --> 40:32.392
Hey, Ray, you want to take some?

40:32.517 --> 40:33.518
Um...

40:33.602 --> 40:35.020
I mean, if you're up for it.

40:35.937 --> 40:37.480
Um...

40:37.564 --> 40:39.316
Yeah?
Sure, right?

40:39.399 --> 40:41.109
Take a couple. I'll be fine.

40:41.192 --> 40:43.778
All right. All right,
get ready, boys! Get ready!

40:43.862 --> 40:45.071
All right.

40:45.196 --> 40:46.448
Okay, you ready?

40:46.573 --> 40:47.949
You guys ready out there?

40:48.074 --> 40:49.200
Bend your knees. Bend your knees.

40:49.492 --> 40:50.785
Take it easy on me.

40:51.286 --> 40:53.163
I haven't swung in a while.

40:58.376 --> 41:00.420
All right, hold on.
Let me loosen up real quick.

41:00.503 --> 41:03.006
- Okay, okay. Next one.
Just let me... Yeah.

41:11.723 --> 41:13.183
Dad?

41:14.226 --> 41:15.268
You okay, boss?

41:15.936 --> 41:16.937
Ooh.

41:17.020 --> 41:19.481
Ray? You okay?

41:19.564 --> 41:22.150
I'm okay.

41:24.236 --> 41:25.654
I'm good. Let's keep going.

41:25.779 --> 41:27.239
- Okay.
I'm good. I'm good.

41:27.322 --> 41:28.740
Shit.

41:28.823 --> 41:30.283
Why don't you throw that again?

41:30.367 --> 41:31.409
All right.

42:13.785 --> 42:15.495
Oh, my God!

42:16.454 --> 42:17.831
Oh, my God!

42:30.051 --> 42:31.928
See, boys, that's how you hit a ball.

42:32.012 --> 42:33.638
That's how you hit it, man.

42:48.945 --> 42:51.615
You know the deal.
Stay in the house, bed by 10:00.

42:51.698 --> 42:53.158
- We'll be back after dinner.
- Mm-hmm.

42:53.241 --> 42:55.035
Don't make me regret not getting a sitter.

42:55.118 --> 42:56.745
Yeah, okay, I know.
- Yeah?

42:57.913 --> 42:59.289
Ray, you ready?

42:59.372 --> 43:00.457
We gotta go.

43:10.050 --> 43:12.802
Hey, someone's coming over in a minute.
It's not a big deal.

43:13.428 --> 43:14.512
Okay.

43:16.973 --> 43:18.391
It's for the swim team.

43:19.935 --> 43:21.019
Okay.

43:32.072 --> 43:33.448
If you tell Mom,

43:33.573 --> 43:36.034
I'm gonna put a Tide POD
in your fish tank.

43:37.661 --> 43:38.870
Okay.

43:40.914 --> 43:41.998
Marco.

43:42.958 --> 43:44.084
Polo.

43:44.167 --> 43:45.502
Marco.

43:45.585 --> 43:47.128
Polo.

43:51.299 --> 43:53.385
Marco. Marco.

43:53.510 --> 43:54.761
Polo.

43:58.014 --> 43:59.766
You're cheating. You opened your eyes.

43:59.891 --> 44:00.892
- Uh-uh.
- Uh-huh.

44:00.976 --> 44:02.310
I mean, you look great with your hair wet.

44:03.853 --> 44:05.355
You're supposed to say "Polo."

44:05.438 --> 44:07.148
-  Polo.
-  Stop.

44:08.942 --> 44:11.027
Okay. Marco.

44:11.695 --> 44:13.071
Polo.

44:15.115 --> 44:16.116
Fish out of water.

44:16.199 --> 44:17.993
Nope.

44:18.952 --> 44:21.037
<i>They want to see you break...</i>

44:21.162 --> 44:22.831
Marco.

44:24.207 --> 44:26.793
Come on. You have to say something back.

44:27.294 --> 44:28.503
Polo.

44:31.298 --> 44:32.966
Marco.

44:33.091 --> 44:36.219
<i>They want to see you break...</i>

44:44.394 --> 44:45.770
Polo.

44:46.479 --> 44:47.772
Marco?

44:54.529 --> 44:57.365
Ronin, stop, please. Marco.

45:02.287 --> 45:03.496
Polo.

45:04.831 --> 45:06.249
I hear you.

45:14.841 --> 45:16.468
You're right there.

45:20.055 --> 45:21.306
Marco. Come on.

45:24.893 --> 45:26.102
Come on.

45:28.688 --> 45:30.232
Got you. No!

45:53.088 --> 45:54.214
Polo.

45:58.134 --> 45:59.678
Ronin, you're dead.

46:58.361 --> 47:00.238
I got you.

47:00.322 --> 47:02.574
Wait, why didn't you call
"fish out of water"?

47:02.657 --> 47:04.117
- Izzy?
- Oh, my God.

47:05.327 --> 47:06.828
- Hey.

47:06.912 --> 47:07.996
Izzy?

47:08.914 --> 47:09.915
Izzy, you okay?

47:10.665 --> 47:12.834
Hey, hey, hey. Talk to me.

47:12.918 --> 47:14.669
Something was down there.
Something grabbed me.

47:14.794 --> 47:16.463
- Something grabbed you?
- Were you not down there?

47:16.880 --> 47:19.257
No. Look, look, it's okay.
Look, I'm right here.

47:19.633 --> 47:20.842
I didn't see anything.

47:20.926 --> 47:22.344
You were only down there
for a couple seconds.

47:22.427 --> 47:24.304
Maybe your foot got stuck
in the pool cleaner.

47:28.183 --> 47:31.019
- Did it?
- I... I don't know. Maybe.

47:32.646 --> 47:34.231
It's okay, all right? It's okay.

47:34.898 --> 47:36.066
There's nothing there.

47:36.149 --> 47:37.150
Izzy!

47:37.234 --> 47:38.735
- Mom and Dad are home!
Shit. Oh, shit.

47:38.818 --> 47:40.195
I didn't tell my parents
you were coming over.

47:40.278 --> 47:41.821
- Oh, wow.
- I'm sorry. You gotta grab your stuff

47:41.905 --> 47:43.448
- and get out the back gate.
- All right.

47:43.531 --> 47:45.158
Well, thanks for inviting me over.

47:47.369 --> 47:49.204
All right, great.
I'll catch you on Saturday?

47:49.287 --> 47:51.331
Uh, Saturday?

47:51.915 --> 47:52.958
The pool party.

47:53.041 --> 47:55.210
- Oh. Yeah.
- All right.

47:59.297 --> 48:02.342
<i>They want to see you break...</i>

48:07.389 --> 48:09.057
The gate won't open.

48:16.022 --> 48:17.190
Izzy.

48:17.983 --> 48:19.943
I know something scared you last night.

48:20.777 --> 48:22.988
I saw the way you got out of the water.

48:23.071 --> 48:24.364
Go away.

